rComments: Class discussion is about him talking about himself . When he gives his opinion, he thinks everything he says is a fact of life. You can do well in this class if you have no problem massaging his ego and telling him he is right rather than asking critical questions and seeing other viewpoints. On top of that his behavior is extremely unprofessional

In my 4 years spent at this university Professor Beiner is THE WORST PROF I HAVE EVER HAD. The lectures put you to sleep, HE CONSTANTLY SHOWS UP late to class and does not care about the students. As well he believes he knows more than any political theorist, as he has denounced authors such as Machiavelli, Hobbes and Rousseau countless times.

One of the most brilliant scholars in political theory you will ever run into.  If you know anything about serious political theory, you will realize that his readings of certain texts  are beyond genius.

Prof. Beiner while very knowledgeable, can at times be very boring and tedious. His descriptions while interesting also take him a while to say. His essays are fair however, and if you do your work you will do fine. I enjoyed the course material despite his monotone. He honestly does look just like Eugene Levy. Poor/average professor at best.
